The gold medal was presented at a ceremony on a Serbian national holiday.  Depp received the award for his “outstanding achievements in public and cultural activities.”  “Particularly in the field of cinema and the promotion of the Republic of Serbia in the world,” Vučić stated according to the Serbian news website. Balkan Insightt. Depp has starred in a number of Serbian productions, the most recent of which was the movie minimum and the animated series puffins† The 58-year-old actor said he was extremely honored to receive the award, calling it a “hugely proud moment” and a “beautiful start to my new life.”  With the latter, he seems to refer to the lawsuit in which he is involved with his ex-wife Amber Heard, who accused him of domestic violence in 2016.  Depp has always denied the allegations, claiming that he was the victim of violence at the hands of Heard. Johnny Depp awarded with honorary medal by Serbian president |  Stars
